&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GYNAECOLOGY SERVICES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAND 2 Clinical Support Workers&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to become part of the dynamic, well established Gynaecology.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have positions in both our Gynaecology ward and Gynaecology Outpatients / Ambulatory unit &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ward J24/24A &lt;/strong&gt;is split into three areas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inpatient surgery,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gynaecology Assessment and Treatment Unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gynaecology Assessment and Treatment Unit Clinic&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outpatients / Ambulatory &lt;/strong&gt;care covers multiple services&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;General Gynaecology clinics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hysteroscopy Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Uro- Gynaecology service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Colposcopy service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recurrent Miscarriage&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fertility control&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come and join our team in Leeds and become part of ‘The Leeds Way’ sharing our vision and values. Our Trust is recognised for our staff engagement, great care and rated &lt;strong&gt;GOOD&lt;/strong&gt; by the Care Quality Commission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust is one of the largest acute health providers in the UK and based in one of the fastest growing and vibrant cities in the north.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Successful candidates must hold a level 2 NVQ in health and social care or an equivalent healthcare related qualification and have experience of working in a hospital care setting.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For all new starters to the Trust we have an award winning, structured Introduction to Professional Practice (IPP) Induction programme to prepare you for working at LTHT. Within the first three months of your role you will be required to complete the Cavendish Care Certificate.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Due to COVID-19 guidelines interviews will take place virtually. If you require any support or wish to trial this beforehand please get in touch.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information contact either: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;J24/24A Jo Cryan Senior sister on 0113 206 9124 email or joanne.cryan@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GOPD / Ambulatory Unit Nicola Hick Senior sister on 0113 206 6424 email or nicola.hick@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Internal care support staff&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; currently employed by Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust, who wish to work in a different area, at the same AfC Band, job description and person specification should contact their Matron and employ the internal transfer process.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We may share information, as appropriate, that you have provided in your application form with external partners or other organisations help to facilitate your recruitment process.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
